        <div class="overlay"></div>
        <h1>The History of Maharishi Mahesh Yogi's<br>Transcendental Meditation Movement<br>in Seelisberg, Switzerland</h1>
        <p>The Age of Enlightenment in the Heart of the Swiss Alps (1970–2026)</p>
        <img class="portrait" src="https://maharishimaheshyogi.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/blog-1.jpg" alt="Maharishi Mahesh Yogi">
    </header>

    <section id="introduction" class="intro">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>Maharishi Mahesh Yogi, founder of the Transcendental Meditation (TM) movement, established Seelisberg as a global hub in the early 1970s. Located high above Lake Lucerne in Canton Uri, this picturesque Swiss village became the international headquarters for TM from approximately 1971–1983.</p>
        <p>Maharishi chose the former Hotel Sonnenberg as the center, transforming it into the Maharishi European Research University (MERU) and later adding the Maharishi Ayurveda Health Centre.</p>

        <div class="gallery">
            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b9/Seelisberg_and_Hotel_Sonnenberg%2C_Lake_Lucerne%2C_Switzerland-LCCN2001703101.jpg" alt="Historical view of Hotel Sonnenberg">
            <img src="https://afar.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/1660df3/2147483647/strip/false/crop/800x450+0+25/resize/1200x675!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fk3-prod-afar-media.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fbrightspot%2Ff8%2Fa8%2F33ccc68a6b7f2087ffd6bfad18cf%2Foriginal-127be8f1f60252154f5ab1dcf0358616.jpg" alt="MERU building">
            <img src="https://www.ayurveda-seelisberg.ch/uploads/images/home-mobile-pilgerheim3-en.jpg" alt="Maharishi Ayurveda Health Centre">
            <img src="https://c8.alamy.com/comp/2RT9XP1/seelisberg-and-hotel-sonnenberg-lake-lucerne-switzerland-1890-2RT9XP1.jpg" alt="Early Hotel Sonnenberg">
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="timeline">
        <h2>Timeline</h2>
        <div class="timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <h3>Early 1970s</h3>
                    <p>Maharishi acquires Hotel Sonnenberg; Seelisberg becomes the world headquarters for the TM movement.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <h3>1975</h3>
                    <p>Founding of MERU for scientific research on TM and higher states of consciousness. Inauguration of the "Dawn of the Age of Enlightenment."</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <h3>1976–1983</h3>
                    <p>Peak years; Maharishi resides and teaches in Seelisberg. Introduction of advanced programs like TM-Sidhi (including Yogic Flying).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <h3>Early 1980s</h3>
                    <p>Launch of Maharishi Ayurveda in Seelisberg – the birthplace of this revived system outside India.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <h3>1990</h3>
                    <p>Global headquarters moves to Vlodrop, Netherlands.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-content">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <h3>2025</h3>
                    <p>The property is sold, marking the end of an era, though TM-related activities continue in the region.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="legacy">
        <h2>Key Events and Legacy</h2>
        <p class="intro">Seelisberg was the epicenter of TM's "golden age." Thousands attended courses, teacher training, and personal lectures by Maharishi. It hosted international conferences blending ancient Vedic knowledge with modern science.</p>
        <p class="intro">The serene Alpine location inspired major developments in the movement, including global programs aimed at creating world peace through collective meditation.</p>

        <blockquote>"Seelisberg is a place of peace and the most creative place in Central Europe." – Maharishi Mahesh Yogi</blockquote>

        <p class="intro">Today, while the main facilities have transitioned (with the Ayurveda Health Centre closing in 2025), the site remains a place of profound historical significance for TM practitioners worldwide.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="location">
        <h2>The Location</h2>
        <p class="intro">Seelisberg offers breathtaking views over Lake Lucerne and the surrounding Alps – a setting that perfectly complemented the pursuit of inner peace.</p>
        <img class="location-img" src="https://c8.alamy.com/comp/2F60JN2/aerial-view-of-the-lake-lucerne-and-the-seelisberg-area-near-the-famous-ruetli-meadow-in-central-switzerland-on-a-sunny-summer-day-2F60JN2.jpg" alt="Aerial view of Lake Lucerne from Seelisberg">

